	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="http://vgwiz.com/" class="postlink">http://vgwiz.com/</a> released their flash cart for the atari 2600, looks pretty cool.
<br />
<br />Doesn't look like it would support every game, but I'd bet it runs the vast majority of them.
<br />
<br />I don't know if anyone else here is interested in that old system.  Myself, I've pretty much always had one (originally as an expansion for the Coleco), I've got about 200 carts for it now.  I wrote a very simple program for it once.
<br />
<br />I got one of vgwiz's 8kB EPROM carts a while back.  Good cart, unfortunately my EPROM emulator doesn't cooperate with the system very well, it puts <em>tons</em> of noise in the video signal (does this on my NES too, but not as badly).  Haven't tried correcting that yet.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
